Mr Rafik Hariri, the new Lebanese prime minister, announced at the weekend a
30-strong, half-Christian, half-Moslem cabinet of which 12 members are
technocrats or business associates of his, writes Lara Marlowe in Beirut.
The prime minister, who has taken the finance portfolio, has appointed Mr
