<HEADLINE>
FT  02 NOV 92 / Release in China
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By YVONNE PRESTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
China has freed a Hong Kong journalist detained in Beijing for almost a week
on charges of stealing state secrets, Yvonne Preston writes from Beijing.
Ms Leung Waiman, a correspondent for the Hong Kong daily Express, was
released at the weekend after she had confessed her guilt, a public security
official said.  She is barred from re-entering China for two-years.
