<HEADLINE>
FT  31 OCT 92 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
JOHANNESBURG ended mixed after a sideways drift for most of the day as the
market looked for fresh factors. Trading picked up slightly towards the
close on month-end position-squaring.
Some shares, like Pick 'n Pay and Amgold were also bought ahead of the last
day to register for dividends.
The overall index was unchanged at 3,017, down slightly on the week. The
industrial index was 3 off at 4,013 and the gold index was up 1 at 816.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
<PAGE>
London Page 21
</PAGE>
