Lawyers for the 85-year-old Mr Clifford have claimed he should not be tried
as he might die as a result of the stress inherent in a court trial. Mr
Morgenthau said that dismissing the Clifford case would be wrong since it
would indicate that 'public figures can manipulate and avoid the US criminal
justice system.'
