FT  31 OCT 92 / TGWU warns on public pay freeze
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR BILL MORRIS, general secretary of the TGWU, Britain's biggest union,
warned yesterday that the government will not get away with a pay freeze in
the public sector.
Mr Morris, speaking at a Labour party local government conference in
Manchester, said: 'A pay freeze means a real wage cut, as simple as that.'
</TEXT>
