FT  31 OCT 92 / Markets: Fillip for smaller companies - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Smaller company shares have continued to benefit from the more cheerful tone
of the markets, in the wake of recent interest rate cuts. The Hoare Govett
Index (capital gains version) rose 0.9 per cent over the week to October 29
from 1075.56 to 1085.44. Meanwhile the County Index also rose 0.9 per cent
from 831.03 to to 838.71 over the same period.
